    <h1>Responsibility of a Scrum master in the MFD Team</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>You must hold your scrum meeting with your team each morning. Th=
is is often done in the MFD War Rooms, however this is not a requirement. T=
his meeting is to allow your team to let you know their progress on tasks, =
and bring up any blocking issues.</p>
<p>You must attend the scrum of scrums, this is a scrum meeting for all of =
the scrum masters to report to Chris Yeomans. Any blocking issues raised by=
 your team that cannot be fixed in your team should be raised here.</p>
<p>Every monday a NPI meeting is held. By the end of day Friday you must pr=
ovide a slide outlining the state of your sprint, a capture of your burndow=
n, and details explaining the progress made.</p>
<p>Scrum masters now also attend the NPI meeting. They are not required to =
attend the entire meeting, and are called in at the appropriate time. This =
is typically about 2pm.</p>
<p>At the end of each sprint there is a sprint review, this is a meeting wi=
th the participants of the scrum of scrums, as well as the GPMs (Mark Garla=
nd, Adam Murphy, Chris Jones) and direct management (Cenk Tugcetin, Gregoir=
e Outters)</p>
    </div>
